# The Four Pillars of AI Software Engineering

Throughout this course, every lesson will connect to one or more of these pillars.

## 1. Software Engineering

Understanding how software systems are designed and built.

Examples include:

* architecture,
* APIs,
* databases,
* testing,
* deployment,
* scalability.

---

## 2. Artificial Intelligence

Understanding AI capabilities and limitations.

Examples include:

* LLMs,
* embeddings,
* RAG,
* vision,
* speech,
* agents,
* prompt engineering.

---

## 3. Product Thinking

Understanding the problem before writing code.

Examples include:

* user stories,
* requirements,
* workflows,
* UX,
* business goals,
* feature prioritization.

---

## 4. Engineering Workflow

Understanding how modern teams build software.

Examples include:

* Git,
* CI/CD,
* code reviews,
* AI-assisted workflows,
* testing,
* deployment,
* monitoring.

